fehd.ADR_EN: G/F., NO. 34 GRAHAM STREET, CENTRAL, HONG KONG
fehd.ADR_TC: 香港中環嘉咸街34號地下

result.adr_address: 34 Graham St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: NOC Graham St.

reviews.text:
This place made art out of Coffee!
If you're a coffee person you have to visit this place.
The attention for details is outstanding, every cup of coffee gets the full attention and love of the brewer.
We also ate a small breakfast which was great and made right in front of our eyes.
Everything is clean and tidy, a really fun experience.
10/10 must visit.
Consistently good at what they do. Make great coffee and teas and well as yummy treat. The cafe is NOT wheelchair or stroller accessible
Quaint, love the decor. Have been a fan of NOC gough st for awhile and as someone visiting the Graham st. for the first time, I'm already in love with it as well. Got the cold brew, great taste.

Cozy little coffee place in Central with good coffee. The food items are a bit limited, mainly items on toast.

The decor is nice and it has an inviting atmosphere.
Probably the best coffee shop in all of Hong Kong. And no, this is not puffery, it's based on spending at entire day taste testing around town.
